## TL;DR: Yellow Cushion Cut Diamond — What to Know First

**A yellow cushion cut diamond concentrates body colour more effectively than any other shape at the same GIA grade — the cushion's large, open-table facets pool yellow saturation in the face-up zone in a way that makes Fancy Yellow read as Fancy Intense when compared side-by-side to a round brilliant at the same GIA colour grade.** This is The Colour Cut Advantage: the cut choice changes how colour is perceived, which means a cushion at Fancy Yellow delivers more visible yellow saturation per dollar than a round at Fancy Intense at the same viewing distance. **→ Best entry pick:** [GIA 1.01ct Fancy Yellow SI2 Cushion Modified at $1,549](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-26394333?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — GIA-certified natural fancy yellow, the lowest price entry for a 1ct yellow cushion cut at Blue Nile.

**Priority:** The colour intensity grade matters more than clarity for yellow cushion cut diamonds. Fancy Yellow SI2 is nearly indistinguishable from Fancy Yellow VS2 face-up, but Fancy Intense Yellow at the same clarity costs 37–111% more. The Intensity Staircase means each step up the GIA colour scale costs exponentially more, not linearly — budget to Fancy Yellow first unless deeper saturation is a non-negotiable priority.

