## The Intensity Staircase

The Intensity Staircase is the non-linear price escalation through GIA's five yellow diamond colour grades — Fancy Light Yellow, Fancy Yellow, Fancy Intense Yellow, Fancy Deep Yellow, and Fancy Vivid Yellow — where each grade step costs disproportionately more than the last. From Fancy Yellow to Fancy Intense Yellow at 1ct, the price step is 37–111% depending on clarity and saturation position within the grade band. From Fancy Intense Yellow to Fancy Vivid Yellow, the step is 3–15x — moving from a retail luxury market into a collector market where per-carat pricing bears no relationship to the pricing at lower grades.

The staircase structure means budget planning requires a grade anchor, not just a carat target. A buyer with $5,000 available for the stone can get a [2ct Fancy Yellow SI2 at $3,636](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-28980659?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) or a [2ct Fancy Yellow VS2 at $5,674](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-28765319?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — both GIA-certified natural cushion cuts with unmistakable yellow colour. The same $5,000 stone budget does not reach a 2ct Fancy Intense Yellow, which starts at [$7,052](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-22116638?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — more than the best 2ct Fancy Yellow VS2 available.

The practical buying rule from The Intensity Staircase: for buyers under $5,000 stone budget, Fancy Yellow is the correct grade anchor. The extra budget available after choosing a well-cut Fancy Yellow SI2 is better spent on carat weight or setting quality than on upgrading to Fancy Intense Yellow at a smaller size. For buyers with $7,000+ available for the stone alone, Fancy Intense Yellow at 2ct becomes competitive — the 2ct FI SI2 at [$7,052](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-22116638?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) delivers visibly deeper saturation than any 2ct Fancy Yellow at the same budget, and saturation is worth prioritising over clarity once the stone is eye-clean.

