## Large Yellow Cushion Cut Diamond — 2ct to 5ct+

Large yellow cushion cut diamonds — 2ct to 5ct+ — represent the collector tier of the fancy yellow market and operate under different pricing logic than the 1ct range. At 2ct Fancy Yellow SI2, the entry is [$3,636](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-28980659?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a significant step from 1ct pricing that reflects both the geometric carat weight premium and the reduced supply of large fancy yellow rough. The 2ct+ tier is also where the clarity premium becomes more meaningful: at 2ct, the jump from SI2 to VS2 represents a genuine face-up quality difference as inclusions are more visible at greater stone depth and face-up area.

At 3ct, Fancy Yellow cushion cuts start from [$9,581](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-27895587?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at SI2 clarity and scale to [$19,520](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-29540948?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at VVS2 — a 2x premium for the clarity upgrade at the same carat and colour grade. Fancy Intense Yellow at 3ct starts from [$18,403](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/yellow-27608843?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — directly competitive with high-clarity Fancy Yellow at equivalent carat. Buyers at the 3ct tier face a meaningful strategic choice between Fancy Yellow VVS and Fancy Intense Yellow SI1 at comparable total spend.

